Description: "(array) Angles of F-coils in degrees measured from the outward directed horizontal.  This assumes the left and right sides of the coil are vertical; only the top and bottom are slanted.  If this variable is not part of the namelist
column4: it will be read from the 5th column of the first NFCOIL lines after the namelist."

Description: "(array) Angles of F-coils in degrees measured from the outward directed horizontal.  This assumes the top and bottom of the coil are horizontal; only the left and right sides are slanted.  It is only used when AF=0.  If this variable is not part of the namelist
column4: it will be read from the 6th column of the first NFCOIL lines after the namelist."

Description: "(array) Angles of magnetic probes in degrees. The measured poloidal magnetic field is given as BR cos(AMP2) + BZ sin(AMP2)."

"(array) Angle of flux loop coils in degrees measured from the outward directed horizontal.  This assumes the left and right sides of the coil are vertical; only the top and bottom are slanted.  If this variable is not part of the namelist
column4: it will be read from the 5th column of the NSILOP lines after the F-coils (if they are not in the namelist)."

Description: "(array) Angle of flux loop coils in degrees measured from the outward directed horizontal.  This assumes the top and bottom of the coil are horizontal; only the left and right sides are slanted.  It is only used when ASI=0.  If this variable is not part of the namelist
column4: it will be read from the 6th column of the NSILOP lines after the F-coils (if they are not in the namelist)."

Description: "(array) Angles of vessel segments in degrees measured from the outward directed horizontal.  This assumes the left and right sides of the coil are vertical; only the top and bottom are slanted.  If this variable is not part of the namelist
column4: it will be read from the 5th column of the first NVESEL lines after the E-coils (if they are not in the namelist)."

Description: "(array) Angles of vessel segments in degrees measured from the outward directed horizontal.  This assumes the top and bottom of the coil are horizontal; only the left and right sides are slanted.  It is only used when AVS=0.  If this variable is not part of the namelist
column4: it will be read from the 6th column of the first NVESEL lines after the E-coils (if they are not in the namelist)."

Description: "(integer array) Indices where E-coil Green functions will be stored in table
column4: it will be read from the 5th column of the first NECOIL lines after the flux loops (if they are not in the namelist)."
